notes.text: The placer group is a model used to group order requests. A receiving system may receive only a placer group (depending on the attribution needed to specify the order) with no explicit observation order component sent in the message. In all cases, a receiving system must be able to act upon the information received.
This is the requested location to perform the service or activity.
For a child (occurrence) request to refer to a parent. Not used in a request message when sending both the parent and some occurrences.

The Common Order model is used to order multiple healthcare services from different diagnostic services such as (Observation, Procedure, Supply, Diet (future) , Pharmacy, Laboratory, Diagnostic Imaging). Property-contextConductionStyle: C
